          "year": 2019,
          "note": "The softest, most sentimental thing Tarantino's made: a day-in-the-life of a fading TV western star (DiCaprio) and his stuntman (Pitt) that rewrites the Manson murders. They read it as a partner film to Jackie Brown; Sean calls Leo's trailer meltdown top-two DiCaprio, and the Julia Butters scene the most tender writing Tarantino's done."
